The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Fortress Hyderabad 

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Hyderabad, March 1: Hyderabad will take on the look of a fortress during President George W. Bushs four-hour flying visit on Friday. The security apparatus in place include:

 Over 30 battalions of security personnel, including CRPF and police

 Surveillance bombers (B-52) and choppers

 High-frequency electronic explosive and mobile jammers

 Radar-supported anti-missile strike establishments

 3,000 snipers

 Begumpet airport to be sealed between 6.30 am and 2-30 pm on Friday. Sixteen incoming and 14 outgoing flights rescheduled

 US Secret Service and US Marines to take over Acharya N.G. Ranga Agricultural University and Indian School of Business on Wednesday-Thursday midnight 

 Bangalore highway and Mumbai highway to be sealed to heavy vehicular traffic 10 km from the universities

 Special invitees to both events to be frisked and given entry passes two hours ahead of programme

 No one, barring US Secret Service and city task force commandos, to be allowed on university premises at time of event. 




